citation.title: Introducing suffix forest for mining tri-clusters from time-series data
citation.authors: Kartick Chandra Mondal, Moumita Ghosh, Rohmatul Fajriyah, Anirban Roy
citation.journal: Innovations in Systems and Software Engineering
citation.description: Three-dimensional data is becoming more prevalent these days. Unsupervised data analysis can be used to find hypothesized patterns of interest from the three-dimensional data. In this context, clustering can be used to group observations along a single dimension, but its usage is restricted in three-dimensional data domains as the observations are significantly connected in subspaces of the overall space. Bi-clustering addresses the issue of subspace clustering but ignores the third dimension. As a result, the concept of tri-clustering, coherent subspaces within three-dimensional data, was introduced. To deal with these issues, tri-clustering, the identification of coherent subspaces within three-dimensional data, has been extensively studied.
